ORANGE BEACH, Ala. (AP) — U.S. Coast Guard crews have suspended the search for an Alabama boater whose vessel was found near a Florida fishing pier with its throttle engaged but no one inside, officials said.The search for John Hayden, 63, was suspended around 6:30 p.m. Tuesday. Crews had searched more than 1,426 nautical miles, The Pensacola News Journal reported.The search began Monday near Fort Pickens in Florida, when Hayden didn’t return as planned after leaving Orange Beach, Alabama. His vessel was found near the Fort Pickens Fishing Pier around 11 a.m. Monday.